# FUTURE_DS_02
📊 Customer Retention & Churn Analysis

📌 Project Overview
This project focuses on analyzing customer churn behavior to identify why customers leave a subscription-based service and how retention can be improved.

Customer retention is a critical metric for subscription businesses, as reducing churn directly impacts revenue, growth, and long-term sustainability.

The goal of this project is to generate data-driven insights and actionable recommendations that can support business decision-making.

🎯 Objectives
Analyze customer churn patterns
Identify high-risk customer segments
Understand customer lifetime behavior
Determine key drivers of churn
Provide actionable business recommendations to improve retention
🛠️ Tools & Technologies
R → Data cleaning, transformation, and statistical analysis
Microsoft Excel → Dashboard creation and data visualization

📁 Dataset
Telco Customer Churn Dataset
Contains 7,000+ customer records with:
Demographics
Subscription details
Service usage
Billing information
Churn status

🔍 Data Preparation (R)
Key steps performed in R:

Converted TotalCharges to numeric
Handled missing values (removed ~0.15% of data)
Converted Churn into a binary variable (0 = retained, 1 = churned)
Performed exploratory data analysis (EDA)
Built a logistic regression model to identify churn drivers

📊 Key Analysis Performed
1. Churn Rate Analysis
Calculated overall churn rate
Identified baseline business performance
2. Customer Segmentation
Churn by:
Contract type
Internet service
Monthly charges
Tenure
3. Customer Lifetime Analysis
Examined how long customers stay before churning
Identified high-risk early-stage customers
4. Statistical Modeling
Applied logistic regression to determine key drivers of churn
Interpreted results using odds ratios

📈 Dashboard (Excel)
An interactive dashboard was created to present insights clearly and support decision-making.

Dashboard Features:
KPI Metrics:
Total Customers
Total Revenue
Average Monthly Charges
Churn Rate
Visualizations:
Churn by Contract Type
Churn by Internet Service
Churn vs Tenure
Customer segmentation insights

🔑 Key Insights
📉 Churn Rate: ~26.5% (≈ 1 in 4 customers leave)
📄 Contract Type: Month-to-month contracts have the highest churn
⏳ Tenure: Most churn occurs within the first 12 months
🌐 Internet Service: Fiber optic users show higher churn rates
💰 Pricing: Higher monthly charges are associated with increased churn

💡 Business Recommendations
Based on the analysis:

Encourage customers to move to long-term contracts
Improve onboarding experience for new customers
Introduce loyalty programs and retention incentives
Review pricing strategies for high-cost plans
Provide proactive support for high-risk customers

